name: Prizrak Nuly
overview: Prizrak Nuly is a Czech language arcade collect 'em up for the Atari 8-bit line of computers, it was developed by Jiri Bernasek and published by BeWeSoft in 1988. Game description: A mix of exploration and collect'em. You steer a little spaceship which has to collect coins with an "1" on them and avoid the floating 0. Crashing against walls, houses or anything else also costs your life.
